data.meta_description: Woody Allen - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document provides a biography of Woody Allen. It discusses that he was born in Brooklyn, New York and began his career as a comedy writer in the 1950s, writing jokes and scripts for television. In the early 1960s, Allen began performing as a stand-up comedian with a persona of an insecure intellectual. He began writing and directing films in the mid-1960s and has directed over 40 films. Allen is known for films such as Annie Hall (1977), Manhattan (1979), and Midnight in Paris (2011). He has won four Academy Awards for screenwriting.
